"I suggest that you folks should consider producing an official
specification of how a domain server's database should distinguish
between different internet addresses."

That approach doesn't feel right to me. First, it means we have to
complicate the name/address database with connectivity information.
Second, connectivity info (at least around here) tends to be a bit more
more dynamic than host addresses.

I think that sort of info should be availiable from the gateways. How
about another ICMP pair? This will make more sense in the future when
routing starts to depend upon Type-Of-Service and/or other fancy things
start to happen.

